Global Funds Sell Net 12.5 Billion Rupees of Indian Derivatives

-- B y   P a r e s h   J a t a k i a
-- 
2011-09-13T03:29:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-13/global-funds-sell-net-12-5-billion-rupees-of-indian-derivatives.html
Global investors sold a net 12.5
billion rupees ($265 million) of Indian equity  derivatives 
yesterday, according to the website of the National Stock
Exchange of India Ltd.  Open interest, or the number of contracts outstanding in
value terms, fell 1 percent to 1.02 trillion rupees, or 40.6
percent of the gross market position, the website showed. Open
interest reached a record 1.6 trillion rupees on Sept. 21.  Foreign funds sold a net 9.35 billion rupees of shares in
the  cash  segment yesterday, according to preliminary data given
by the bourse.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paresh Jatakia in Mumbai at 
 pareshj@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Arijit Ghosh at 
